        <updateDate>2017-03-21T18:10:45Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Help End Assault Rifle Tragedies Act of 2016</b> <b>or the HEART Act</b></p> <p>This bill amends the federal criminal code to make it a crime to knowingly transfer, loan, or dispose of a machinegun or semiautomatic assault weapon to an individual who is known or reasonably believed to be less than 16 years of age.</p> <p>It defines the term &quot;semiautomatic assault weapon.&quot; </p> <p>A violator is subject to a fine, up to 10 years in prison, or both.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
